features: [Storage Aplenty] This versatile plastic shoe storage organizer, able to accommodate up to 24 pairs of shoes, doubles as storage for bags and clothing. Its space-efficient side hooks offer a handy spot to hang hats or dog leashes

[Robust and Secure] Crafted with premium connectors, durable plastic panels, and strong steel wire, each slot of this shoe storage cabinet holds up to 11 lb. The provided anti-tip kit ensures safe use in living rooms or bedrooms

[Easy Assembly and Disassembly] The included rubber mallet makes assembling this shoe rack quick and easy. This organizer can also be quickly disassembled to store or transport, letting you easily rearrange this around your home

[Adaptable and Versatile] Configure this storage unit in different ways. Make it have 2 or 3 separate rows, or even divide it into 2 small shelf units to organize shoes, clothes, or toiletries in your entryway, bathroom, or any other desired space

[Ventilated and Easy to Clean] This plastic shoe cabinet features clear doors, providing dust-proof and waterproof protection while allowing easy viewing of shoes inside. Grommets on the doors enable effortless opening and promote ventilation

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good for price
reviews.reviewText: This shoe rack was super easy to put together my 8 year old and I put it together in under 40 minutes and I purchased the largest option. All the pieces are plastic but aren’t super cheap, the shoe rack isn’t super solid but that doesn’t have to do with the construction of it more because the material isn’t wood or something more solid which I thought was going to bother me more with being a family of 6 and four of those six are two older children and a husband with large work boots, works great. Looks esthetically pleasing! We also just purchased this again 6 this time to add on for more space for shoes (we have a large family lol).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Neat shoe organizer, good quality.
reviews.reviewText: I think this is priced right, the quality is very good, the box is sturdy and has a lot of space inside each compartment. It fits big boots easily, although you may only be able to fit one pair in each if your boot is big. I was skeptical of the quality and build, but I like it so much I am going to order another one so i can store my family's shoes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A Must Buy Shoe Rack
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the SONGMICS Shoe Rack and have been quite impressed with its functionality. What stands out the most is the spacious design of each cube, comfortably accommodating two pairs of shoes instead of just one, effectively doubling the storage capacity. The doors on the unit are remarkably easy to use, allowing for quick and hassle-free access to the shoes. My only critique is the limited color option; the rack is only available in white, which, while sleek, can show dirt quite easily. Offering this shoe rack in more colors would be a great improvement, as it would cater to different interior styles and preferences. Overall, this organizer is a practical and efficient solution for shoe storage, especially for those needing to maximize space

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars perfect to keep shoes organized and clean
reviews.reviewText: My shoes have been stacked & piled on various types of shoe racks over the years, none of which worked quite right for me. I'm glad to finally find one that will keep them organized AND clean! It wasn't hard to put together but it took awhile. A tool is included that will help get it done. It says 8 cubes (which makes it sound like 8 individual, standalone cubes) but it's really 4 cubes that are double wide with a divider in the middle, and double tall, so each cube has room for 4 pairs of shoes. It all snaps together snugly and is fairly sturdy. The solid top, bottom, & sides are all soft vinyl. It feels good, but I'd be very careful about putting too much weight directly on the vinyl as it would probably eventually tear where it connects to the frame. I keep wanting to set stuff on the top of the unit, but have to remind myself to stop. The weight of shoes is fine, but probably not a heavy pile of clothes. My only complaint is that it comes with 4 cubes and my closet space is only tall enough to stack 3 of them, so I have the 4th extra cube that I'd like to use somewhere else, but there's only 1 piece of the top/bottom vinyl so it can't be used as standalone unit (unless the top or bottom is left open, which sort of defeats the purpose of keeping the dust out). I contacted the manufacturer directly and they don't (or won't) ship just that 1 extra piece. Kinda pisses me off cuz I know they've got it. They just won't provide it. The unit "looks" modular, and could very easily BE modular, but it's missing that one piece that pretty much makes it HAVE to be used in just that 1 configuration that's shown in the picture (4 cubes high, each of them double wide). I'm still giving it 5 stars because I do love the 3 pieces I can use, but protesting that one annoying design flaw. (Manufacturer, are you reading this??)

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Holds a LOT of shoes
reviews.reviewText: It got all of my wife's normal shoes (not boots) off the floor and out of those ridiculous hanging things. Fits under clothes, keeps shoes together, away from the dogs, the tile, and anything else that can happen to un-corralled shoes in a closet. Not completely sold on the plastic shelf hooks, but they seem to work and hold shoes. Must be why I'm not an engineer.🤣
